		<div id="comment_body_64960785">At the very bottom and the very top wage increases are keeping pace with inflation, but if you're in the middle (or what's left of it) you're getting squeezed hard by the increased cost of housing, healthcare and education. And if you're at the bottom yes, you're wages are technically increasing more than inflation but that's only because they were dangerously low to begin with. <br> <br>

We're like sharks. If we stop moving we stop breathing and we die. You don't get to just settle into a nice life anymore. There</div>
	</div>

